The paper deals with the problem of pilot beam pattern design for channel estimation in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm also takes into account the spatial and temporal channel correlation, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MM) and large-scale data analysis (cs.LG).
